# Initial setup

-   Install `postgresql`

-   Generate ssh keys (https://help.github.com/articles/generating-ssh-keys):

        ssh-keygen -t rsa -C "your_email@example.com"

-   Clone repo:

        mkdir -p /maco/rails/apps
        cd /maco/rails/apps
        git clone git@bitbucket.org:urbas/trainerjimserver.git

-   User RVM to install latest Ruby & Rails:

        \curl -L https://get.rvm.io | bash -s stable --ruby

    Note: I had to install the following first:

        yum -y install automake autoconf gcc gcc-c++ openssl



## Updating the server with most recent code:
cd /maco/rails/apps/trainerjim && git pull && bundle exec rake db:migrate assets:precompile RAILS_ENV=production && touch /maco/rails/apps/trainerjim/tmp/restart.txt
